vibe_prompt: Build a simple calculator, which sould have minimum features : basic arithmetic operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide), number input, display result, clear function

stories.title: Number Input
stories.description: As a user, I want to input numbers so that I can perform calculations

stories.title: Addition Operation
stories.description: As a user, I want to add two numbers so that I can get their sum

stories.title: Subtraction Operation
stories.description: As a user, I want to subtract one number from another so that I can get the difference

stories.title: Multiplication Operation
stories.description: As a user, I want to multiply two numbers so that I can get their product

stories.title: Division Operation
stories.description: As a user, I want to divide one number by another so that I can get the quotient

stories.title: Result Display
stories.description: As a user, I want to see the calculation result so that I know the answer

stories.title: Clear Function
stories.description: As a user, I want to clear the input and result so that I can start a new calculation

stories.title: Decimal Input
stories.description: As a user, I want to input decimal numbers so that I can perform precise calculations

stories.title: Error Handling for Division by Zero
stories.description: As a user, I want to see an error message when dividing by zero so that I avoid incorrect results

data.summary: Build a simple calculator with basic arithmetic operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide), number input, result display, and clear function to enable users to perform everyday calculations efficiently.

data.architecture_notes: Simple REST API for calculator. Single Calculation model stores operands, operation, result, timestamp. POST /calculate handles all operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide) with validation for division by zero. GET endpoints provide history. DELETE endpoints support clear functionality. Frontend handles input, display, and error messages.

files.description: Main FastAPI app with calculator endpoints

data.setup_instructions: pip install fastapi uvicorn && uvicorn main:app --reload

files.description: Main HTML page with calculator UI, inline CSS/JS, supports basic operations, error handling, and clear function

data.setup_instructions: Open index.html in browser (ensure backend is running at http://localhost:8000 for API calls)

test_cases.notes: Addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division (non-zero) function correctly via API and UI.
Backend returns 400 error with message; frontend displays error appropriately.
Input fields accept decimals via step='any'; backend processes floats correctly.
Clear button empties input fields and resets result display as required.
UI shows calculation results or error messages dynamically after operations.

data.summary: All high and medium priority user stories are satisfied. Implementation is functional and meets core requirements.
recommendations: Add input validation for non-numeric characters in frontend.
Consider persisting calculations to a database instead of memory for production.
Improve UI with a history panel showing past calculations using the GET endpoints.
